    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-28T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-28T05:00:00-05:00" n="420"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6176/22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-28T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 28, 1936—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 28—5:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>448. The facts enumerated in your 348, September 26, 11 a.m., I understand were
                    fully covered in the lengthy conversation which took place on September 24. I
                    accordingly venture to suggest in view of the nature of the conversation
                    reported in my 442, September 24, 5 p.m., that it would serve no useful purpose
                    to reopen the matter by reiterating ground already covered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
